-- Ryder Hesjedal Becomes First Canadian to Win Major Cycling Tour
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2012-05-27T16:29:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-27/ryder-hesjedal-becomes-first-canadian-to-win-major-cycling-tour.html
Ryder Hesjedal today became the first
Canadian to win one of the three major tours of the cycling
season with victory in the Giro d’Italia.   Hesjedal clinched the title after today’s time trial helped
him overtake leader Joaquim Rodriguez of  Spain , who finished
second overall. Hesjedal clocked 34 minutes, 15 seconds for the
17.5-mile stage, for a winning margin of 16 seconds.   Today’s 21st and final stage in Milan was won by Marco 
Pinotti of  Italy . The other “grand tours” are those of France
and Spain.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  